1
00:01:25,800 --> 00:01:34,950
[LIVE UP TO YOUR YOUTH]

2
00:01:35,340 --> 00:01:37,930
[Episode 9]

3
00:01:38,400 --> 00:01:39,270
Ranran,

4
00:01:39,450 --> 00:01:41,920
becoming a great superstar is

5
00:01:42,680 --> 00:01:44,140
just around the corner!

6
00:01:44,200 --> 00:01:45,120
-Nice!
-Nice!

7
00:01:45,140 --> 00:01:45,740
Well said!

8
00:01:46,070 --> 00:01:46,729
Bravo.

9
00:01:47,120 --> 00:01:48,370
I'll drink this third glass for her.

10
00:01:48,370 --> 00:01:49,370
-No, no!
-Come on.

11
00:01:50,450 --> 00:01:52,039
This is my celebratory dinner.

12
00:01:52,039 --> 00:01:53,300
Can't break the rules.

13
00:01:53,400 --> 00:01:53,870
That's right!

14
00:01:53,870 --> 00:01:54,200
OK.

15
00:01:55,090 --> 00:01:55,550
Come on.

16
00:01:55,600 --> 00:01:56,039
Let's drink with her.

17
00:01:56,039 --> 00:01:57,370
-Cheers! Come on!
-Cheers!

18
00:01:57,370 --> 00:01:58,300
Cheers! Cheers!

19
00:01:59,090 --> 00:01:59,950
-Congrats!
-Congrats!

20
00:01:59,950 --> 00:02:00,780
Congrats!

21
00:02:00,840 --> 00:02:01,440
Thank you!

22
00:02:05,480 --> 00:02:07,060
Look how lively it is!

23
00:02:07,150 --> 00:02:08,550
I heard you from outside!

24
00:02:09,360 --> 00:02:11,060
You haven't touched the food.
Waiting for me?

25
00:02:11,060 --> 00:02:11,800
Sit, sit.

26
00:02:12,180 --> 00:02:13,680
Grab a chair. There's one over there.

27
00:02:13,680 --> 00:02:15,430
You know what, I didn't come for nothing.

28
00:02:15,430 --> 00:02:16,500
Here's another dish for you.

29
00:02:16,500 --> 00:02:17,020
Come on.

30
00:02:17,810 --> 00:02:18,810
This is great.

31
00:02:18,810 --> 00:02:19,540
Refreshing.

32
00:02:21,360 --> 00:02:21,930
Just a little.

33
00:02:21,930 --> 00:02:22,790
Zhuang Zhuang,

34
00:02:22,930 --> 00:02:24,130
here's a toast to you.

35
00:02:25,030 --> 00:02:25,900
Thanks for styling

36
00:02:25,900 --> 00:02:27,300
so many beautiful outfits for me.

37
00:02:27,300 --> 00:02:28,000
It was nothing.

38
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:29,210
-I'll chug it. You don't have to.
-Pace yourself.

39
00:02:29,210 --> 00:02:30,410
Don't drink too much.

40
00:02:30,460 --> 00:02:31,590
Count me in. Come on.

41
00:02:32,210 --> 00:02:34,390
Ranran is an honest drinker.

42
00:02:35,079 --> 00:02:37,010
Drinking manners show character.

43
00:02:37,310 --> 00:02:38,510
Downing every glass.

44
00:02:38,590 --> 00:02:39,930
I feel so great today.

45
00:02:40,710 --> 00:02:41,500
Well,

46
00:02:41,620 --> 00:02:42,579
since I came to Beijing...

47
00:02:42,579 --> 00:02:43,500
Can you drink less?

48
00:02:43,500 --> 00:02:45,780
-I've been holding this grudge in my heart.
-I'm fine.

49
00:02:45,780 --> 00:02:47,310
Now I've finally let it out.

50
00:02:47,740 --> 00:02:48,190
No.

51
00:02:49,240 --> 00:02:50,240
I can't hold it in.

52
00:02:50,590 --> 00:02:51,520
Need to throw up?

53
00:02:51,780 --> 00:02:52,710
No, Zhuang.

54
00:02:53,860 --> 00:02:55,590
I mean, I can't hold my words in.

55
00:02:56,370 --> 00:02:56,810
Then say it.

56
00:02:56,810 --> 00:02:57,150
Ranran,

57
00:02:57,150 --> 00:02:58,990
say whatever you want.

58
00:02:59,130 --> 00:02:59,840
Just don't throw up.

59
00:02:59,840 --> 00:03:01,180
-In front of such a feast...
-No! Throw up!

60
00:03:01,180 --> 00:03:01,980
Throw up all you want!

61
00:03:01,980 --> 00:03:03,080
I'm sitting right here.

62
00:03:03,080 --> 00:03:03,750
Throw up all you want.

63
00:03:03,750 --> 00:03:04,500
You're gross.

64
00:03:04,500 --> 00:03:05,370
Will you catch it with your mouth?

65
00:03:05,370 --> 00:03:06,170
I'll catch it!

66
00:03:07,910 --> 00:03:08,780
What's going on?

67
00:03:08,780 --> 00:03:09,150
No.

68
00:03:09,370 --> 00:03:10,170
-Give it to me.
-Shen.

69
00:03:10,170 --> 00:03:10,970
The microphone!

70
00:03:10,970 --> 00:03:11,650
The microphone.

71
00:03:11,650 --> 00:03:12,580
The microphone.

72
00:03:12,750 --> 00:03:13,150
Mic...

73
00:03:14,030 --> 00:03:14,570
She's...

74
00:03:14,800 --> 00:03:15,620
She's on stage!

75
00:03:15,620 --> 00:03:17,060
Come on, let's give her a big hand!

76
00:03:17,060 --> 00:03:18,060
Come on, applaud!

77
00:03:19,300 --> 00:03:20,300
Quiet, everyone.

78
00:03:22,020 --> 00:03:25,690
I came from Huzhou to Beijing,

79
00:03:27,180 --> 00:03:30,520
and moved into this Seasons Change Hostel.

80
00:03:31,590 --> 00:03:32,720
After all this time,

81
00:03:33,079 --> 00:03:35,930
I've never been this happy before.

82
00:03:36,590 --> 00:03:37,990
Never been this excited.

83
00:03:38,140 --> 00:03:39,100
Hear, hear.

84
00:03:39,130 --> 00:03:40,130
My friends,

85
00:03:40,870 --> 00:03:41,860
do you know what?

86
00:03:43,280 --> 00:03:44,010
I've made it!

87
00:03:44,180 --> 00:03:45,579
I've succeeded!

88
00:03:47,150 --> 00:03:48,590
I didn't understand a word you said.

89
00:03:48,590 --> 00:03:49,130
She said she's succeeded.

90
00:03:49,130 --> 00:03:50,650
Actors must speak in Standard Mandarin.

91
00:03:50,650 --> 00:03:51,670
I've made it!

92
00:03:51,970 --> 00:03:52,960
Did you hear me?

93
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:54,890
We heard you!

94
00:03:55,079 --> 00:03:56,340
We heard you this time.

95
00:03:56,860 --> 00:03:57,340
Why...

96
00:03:58,210 --> 00:03:59,600
did I succeed?

97
00:04:00,460 --> 00:04:02,460
Because I always held on to the faith

98
00:04:02,530 --> 00:04:04,000
that I am a good actress.

99
00:04:05,500 --> 00:04:06,190
At 7,

100
00:04:06,250 --> 00:04:08,110
in the Children's Palace Dance Competition,

101
00:04:08,110 --> 00:04:09,240
I was the runner-up.

102
00:04:09,800 --> 00:04:10,950
My backflip kick

103
00:04:11,090 --> 00:04:12,810
made the judges' jaws drop.

104
00:04:13,430 --> 00:04:14,890
I sang, acted, and fought.

105
00:04:15,780 --> 00:04:18,040
The applause was thunderous.

106
00:04:18,300 --> 00:04:19,370
Thunderous!

107
00:04:19,390 --> 00:04:22,510
Thunderous, just thunderous!

108
00:04:23,180 --> 00:04:23,980
At 10,

109
00:04:24,190 --> 00:04:25,500
I'd already made an appearance

110
00:04:25,500 --> 00:04:26,330
in movies.

111
00:04:26,830 --> 00:04:27,650
At 12,

112
00:04:28,130 --> 00:04:29,750
I was already a child star.

113
00:04:30,060 --> 00:04:31,150
And at 17,

114
00:04:31,250 --> 00:04:32,409
a director

115
00:04:32,980 --> 00:04:33,640
cast me

116
00:04:33,690 --> 00:04:34,630
to play

117
00:04:34,630 --> 00:04:35,710
a major role.

118
00:04:36,560 --> 00:04:37,250
But I was

119
00:04:38,480 --> 00:04:40,800
replaced by someone with connections.

120
00:04:43,159 --> 00:04:44,510
Knowing the danger,

121
00:04:45,680 --> 00:04:47,190
I marched right into the tiger's den!

122
00:04:47,190 --> 00:04:49,090
My artist dream

123
00:04:49,240 --> 00:04:51,440
flew and flew,

124
00:04:51,830 --> 00:04:53,500
like a young eagle,

125
00:04:53,980 --> 00:04:55,240
all the way to Beijing.

126
00:04:55,450 --> 00:04:56,980
Dived right into this city!

127
00:04:57,250 --> 00:04:59,480
Unafraid of the storms and rolling waves.

128
00:04:59,480 --> 00:05:00,870
I am a good actress.

129
00:05:01,500 --> 00:05:02,360
I believe in it,

130
00:05:02,770 --> 00:05:04,570
and you should believe in it too.

131
00:05:04,950 --> 00:05:06,970
My artist dream

132
00:05:07,220 --> 00:05:08,900
will bloom brilliantly,

133
00:05:09,130 --> 00:05:10,480
flourishing in full glory!

134
00:05:10,480 --> 00:05:11,480
-Nice!
-Bravo!

135
00:05:11,510 --> 00:05:12,330
Nice!

136
00:05:12,810 --> 00:05:13,210
Bravo!

137
00:05:13,240 --> 00:05:14,030
Well said!

138
00:05:14,130 --> 00:05:16,590
I've yearned for Beijing
since I was little,

139
00:05:16,930 --> 00:05:17,980
singing every day:

140
00:05:17,980 --> 00:05:20,490
"I love Beijing Tiananmen.

141
00:05:20,810 --> 00:05:22,300
The sun rises above Tianan..."

142
00:05:22,300 --> 00:05:25,200
"I love Beijing Tiananmen.

143
00:05:25,240 --> 00:05:29,430
The sun rises above Tiananmen.

144
00:05:29,500 --> 00:05:31,750
The great leader Chairman Mao

145
00:05:31,930 --> 00:05:35,920
leads all of us forward."

146
00:05:51,680 --> 00:05:52,480
Morning, sir.

147
00:05:52,480 --> 00:05:53,010
Morning.

148
00:05:55,450 --> 00:05:56,250
Morning, sir.

149
00:06:11,560 --> 00:06:12,300
Production Assistant?

150
00:06:12,300 --> 00:06:13,680
Here! I'm here!

151
00:06:15,560 --> 00:06:16,660
Your job today

152
00:06:16,800 --> 00:06:18,270
is to clean up this car.

153
00:06:18,750 --> 00:06:19,280
This car?

154
00:06:19,510 --> 00:06:21,250
Yes. We need it soon.

155
00:06:21,300 --> 00:06:21,990
OK, sure!

156
00:06:22,120 --> 00:06:23,980
Here are the keys to the prop room.

157
00:06:25,620 --> 00:06:26,570
I'm going to test drive it.

158
00:06:26,570 --> 00:06:27,450
Drive safe!

159
00:06:27,500 --> 00:06:28,070
Sure!

160
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:31,630
Look at this dust.

161
00:06:31,630 --> 00:06:32,980
Look at all this dust in here.

162
00:06:32,980 --> 00:06:33,430
You...

163
00:06:34,120 --> 00:06:34,870
Hey, Lin.

164
00:06:34,870 --> 00:06:35,740
I don't mean to lecture you.

165
00:06:35,740 --> 00:06:36,420
Every day, you come to me

166
00:06:36,420 --> 00:06:37,620
asking for manpower and money,

167
00:06:37,620 --> 00:06:38,159
but your props

168
00:06:38,159 --> 00:06:39,140
are this shoddy?

169
00:06:39,270 --> 00:06:39,950
No, Manager.

170
00:06:39,950 --> 00:06:40,659
Don't be mad.

171
00:06:40,659 --> 00:06:41,250
Look.

172
00:06:41,390 --> 00:06:42,690
It'll surely look better tomorrow.

173
00:06:42,690 --> 00:06:43,300
If it doesn't,

174
00:06:43,300 --> 00:06:44,560
I'll get someone else to do this.

175
00:06:44,560 --> 00:06:46,159
No, please, don't, Manager!

176
00:06:46,250 --> 00:06:46,930
Come here.

177
00:06:46,950 --> 00:06:47,850
Come on.

178
00:06:48,630 --> 00:06:49,450
Wait a second.

179
00:06:56,600 --> 00:06:57,330
My cousin just

180
00:06:57,330 --> 00:06:58,370
came from our hometown.

181
00:06:58,370 --> 00:07:00,570
He brought you some local specialties.

182
00:07:00,920 --> 00:07:01,430
Not here.

183
00:07:01,430 --> 00:07:02,760
Send it to my room later.

184
00:07:05,100 --> 00:07:05,630
Manager.

185
00:07:05,920 --> 00:07:07,330
Is that new production assistant

186
00:07:07,330 --> 00:07:08,330
a relative of the director?

187
00:07:08,330 --> 00:07:09,370
What relative?

188
00:07:09,370 --> 00:07:11,630
I heard he's just an amateur enthusiast.

189
00:07:11,740 --> 00:07:12,810
The director pitied him,

190
00:07:12,810 --> 00:07:14,360
so he let him join the crew
to give him a shot.

191
00:07:14,360 --> 00:07:15,830
This kid hasn't done anything before.

192
00:07:15,830 --> 00:07:17,130
He's bound to screw up sooner or later.

193
00:07:17,130 --> 00:07:17,980
I'll tell you what.

194
00:07:17,980 --> 00:07:18,860
Once he makes a mistake,

195
00:07:18,860 --> 00:07:20,040
I'll mention it to the director

196
00:07:20,040 --> 00:07:20,720
that he isn't

197
00:07:20,720 --> 00:07:21,650
cut out for this.

198
00:07:22,010 --> 00:07:23,610
And that will be the end of it.

199
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:25,060
I'm just worried

200
00:07:25,060 --> 00:07:26,100
that with him

201
00:07:26,240 --> 00:07:27,240
taking the spot,

202
00:07:27,240 --> 00:07:29,300
what I asked you for will be hopeless.

203
00:07:29,330 --> 00:07:30,060
No way.

204
00:07:32,190 --> 00:07:32,720
Manager.

205
00:07:33,220 --> 00:07:33,720
Lin.

206
00:07:41,810 --> 00:07:43,010
Not cut out for it?

207
00:07:44,420 --> 00:07:47,130
I've never seen anyone
more cut out for it than me.

208
00:07:47,130 --> 00:07:49,900
[East Shore Club]

209
00:08:18,010 --> 00:08:19,470
Hello. Are you Ms. Zhang?

210
00:08:21,930 --> 00:08:22,790
Uh... No, I'm not.

211
00:08:22,790 --> 00:08:23,740
Then you can't sit here.

212
00:08:23,740 --> 00:08:25,150
This table is reserved.

213
00:08:27,630 --> 00:08:28,980
I... I'm waiting for someone.

214
00:08:28,980 --> 00:08:30,100
I'll leave right away.

215
00:08:30,100 --> 00:08:31,200
You can sit for a while.

216
00:08:31,200 --> 00:08:32,390
But you have to order something.

217
00:08:32,390 --> 00:08:33,520
What would you like?

218
00:08:36,630 --> 00:08:37,150
I...

219
00:08:38,490 --> 00:08:39,900
I-I'll have a soda.

220
00:08:40,169 --> 00:08:41,030
The rule is that

221
00:08:41,549 --> 00:08:42,940
you can only order alcohol.

222
00:08:42,940 --> 00:08:43,289
But

223
00:08:43,620 --> 00:08:45,170
aren't they drinking soda?

224
00:08:45,630 --> 00:08:46,750
They are regulars.

225
00:08:46,840 --> 00:08:47,970
How is that the same?

226
00:08:48,220 --> 00:08:49,150
What'd you like?

227
00:08:50,130 --> 00:08:51,410
Why are you discriminating against me?

228
00:08:51,410 --> 00:08:52,760
What discrimination?

229
00:08:53,080 --> 00:08:53,910
Hey, this is a bar!

230
00:08:53,910 --> 00:08:55,170
What'd you order if not alcohol?

231
00:08:55,170 --> 00:08:55,790
Order you?

232
00:08:55,940 --> 00:08:57,430
How could you say that?

233
00:08:57,460 --> 00:08:58,270
What'd I say wrong?

234
00:08:58,270 --> 00:08:59,630
Everyone, come and take a look.

235
00:08:59,630 --> 00:09:01,030
This woman is a freeloader.

236
00:09:01,030 --> 00:09:02,640
She wouldn't order anything.

237
00:09:02,640 --> 00:09:04,360
I just said I'm ordering a soda!

238
00:09:04,360 --> 00:09:05,240
Did you hear me?

239
00:09:05,260 --> 00:09:06,250
Apologize to me!

240
00:09:06,290 --> 00:09:07,010
Stop insulting me,

241
00:09:07,010 --> 00:09:07,370
OK?

242
00:09:07,370 --> 00:09:08,270
I'm done talking to you.

243
00:09:08,270 --> 00:09:09,220
Please leave now.

244
00:09:09,220 --> 00:09:10,170
You're not welcome here.

245
00:09:10,170 --> 00:09:10,960
Don't touch me!

246
00:09:10,960 --> 00:09:12,490
Move! Come outside with me!

247
00:09:12,620 --> 00:09:14,050
-Why should I apologize?
-Cut it out.

248
00:09:14,050 --> 00:09:14,840
Why are you dragging me?

249
00:09:14,840 --> 00:09:16,170
Make him apologize to me!

250
00:09:16,170 --> 00:09:16,940
She's my friend.

251
00:09:16,940 --> 00:09:17,620
Apologize to me!

252
00:09:17,620 --> 00:09:18,120
Ranran. Ranran.

253
00:09:18,120 --> 00:09:18,910
I'll apologize to you.

254
00:09:18,910 --> 00:09:19,840
I'll apologize.

255
00:09:20,100 --> 00:09:20,580
Ranran!

256
00:09:21,410 --> 00:09:21,980
You hit my tooth.

257
00:09:21,980 --> 00:09:22,930
Let go of me!

258
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:24,010
I'll apologize to you.

259
00:09:24,010 --> 00:09:26,050
You don't know the situation at all!

260
00:09:26,140 --> 00:09:27,460
It was clearly their fault!

261
00:09:27,460 --> 00:09:28,730
It is their fault!

262
00:09:29,010 --> 00:09:30,410
Isn't my apology enough?

263
00:09:31,030 --> 00:09:32,960
Do you know what they said about me?

264
00:09:33,220 --> 00:09:35,020
They said I was soliciting here.

265
00:09:35,840 --> 00:09:37,370
It's obviously a rip-off joint.

266
00:09:37,370 --> 00:09:37,890
I'm going to find...

267
00:09:37,890 --> 00:09:38,600
No, don't!

268
00:09:39,460 --> 00:09:40,100
You have no idea

269
00:09:40,100 --> 00:09:41,840
how many guests have complained about him.

270
00:09:41,840 --> 00:09:42,550
He won't last long.

271
00:09:42,550 --> 00:09:43,440
They'll get rid of him soon.

272
00:09:43,440 --> 00:09:44,770
He's hurting business.

273
00:09:44,870 --> 00:09:46,500
He is the boss's relative.

274
00:09:46,740 --> 00:09:48,290
If you go complain about him now,

275
00:09:48,290 --> 00:09:49,890
I'll lose my job too, won't I?

276
00:09:50,620 --> 00:09:51,630
On behalf of my boss,

277
00:09:51,630 --> 00:09:52,220
the bar,

278
00:09:52,480 --> 00:09:53,750
and on his behalf, I'll apologize to you.

279
00:09:53,750 --> 00:09:54,350
I'm sorry.

280
00:09:54,370 --> 00:09:55,290
I apologize, OK?

281
00:09:55,290 --> 00:09:56,370
It's my fault. I'm sorry.

282
00:09:56,370 --> 00:09:57,700
You always take other people's sides.

283
00:09:57,700 --> 00:09:58,980
I didn't...

284
00:09:59,100 --> 00:10:00,020
Get out of my way.

285
00:10:00,020 --> 00:10:00,700
Move.

286
00:10:06,910 --> 00:10:08,480
Watch where you're going.

287
00:10:30,010 --> 00:10:31,210
Why did you come here?

288
00:10:32,060 --> 00:10:33,030
To see me?

289
00:10:34,440 --> 00:10:35,170
I forgot to ask you.

290
00:10:35,170 --> 00:10:36,970
How was my performance just now?

291
00:10:40,010 --> 00:10:40,960
It was OK.

292
00:10:41,220 --> 00:10:42,070
Come anytime.

293
00:10:42,410 --> 00:10:43,340
Mention my name.

294
00:10:44,100 --> 00:10:46,230
Listen all you want, and sit anywhere.

295
00:10:46,460 --> 00:10:47,720
You're just bragging.

296
00:10:48,200 --> 00:10:50,000
I'm never coming back
to this rip-off joint.

297
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:51,700
Then where do you want to listen?

298
00:10:51,700 --> 00:10:53,320
I'll play for you there.

299
00:10:55,870 --> 00:10:56,340
I want to go

300
00:10:56,340 --> 00:10:57,870
to the lotus pond to listen.

301
00:10:58,370 --> 00:11:00,970
Then I'll sit on a lotus
and play the sax for you.

302
00:11:02,390 --> 00:11:02,840
Wouldn't I...

303
00:11:02,840 --> 00:11:04,500
Wouldn't I become Nezha then?

304
00:11:06,100 --> 00:11:07,170
You have the Wind and Fire Wheels?

305
00:11:07,170 --> 00:11:08,460
I do have the Wind and Fire Wheels.

306
00:11:08,460 --> 00:11:09,630
You've ridden them.

307
00:11:09,670 --> 00:11:10,650
Either on the crossbar,

308
00:11:10,650 --> 00:11:11,500
or on the back seat.

309
00:11:11,500 --> 00:11:13,550
-I'll kick the wheels...
-Enough fibbing.

310
00:11:13,550 --> 00:11:14,500
Hurry back.

311
00:11:14,510 --> 00:11:15,390
The customers are waiting for you.

312
00:11:15,390 --> 00:11:16,450
I'm not going back.

313
00:11:16,890 --> 00:11:18,630
With you upset and angry,

314
00:11:18,630 --> 00:11:19,760
why should I go back?

315
00:11:19,770 --> 00:11:20,700
I quit. I'm done.

316
00:11:21,940 --> 00:11:22,940
Quit?

317
00:11:23,580 --> 00:11:24,670
It's so hard to find a job nowadays.

318
00:11:24,670 --> 00:11:25,870
Go back immediately!

319
00:11:28,270 --> 00:11:29,750
My performance is over.

320
00:11:29,860 --> 00:11:31,660
It's someone else's turn now.

321
00:11:34,530 --> 00:11:35,750
You're so annoying!

322
00:11:37,410 --> 00:11:38,740
I... I'll walk you back.

323
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:42,000
Let's go then.

324
00:11:42,820 --> 00:11:43,580
Perfect timing.

325
00:11:43,580 --> 00:11:44,640
You should take a break too.

326
00:11:44,640 --> 00:11:46,640
You've been playing the sax all day.

327
00:11:47,900 --> 00:11:49,360
Let's go find the lotuses.

328
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:51,000
Hurry up and come.

329
00:11:51,630 --> 00:11:52,770
I know where there are lotuses

330
00:11:52,770 --> 00:11:53,630
ready to bloom!

331
00:11:59,050 --> 00:11:59,860
Just now,

332
00:12:00,600 --> 00:12:01,360
didn't we say

333
00:12:01,910 --> 00:12:02,460
we were

334
00:12:03,080 --> 00:12:04,280
looking for lotuses?

335
00:12:05,120 --> 00:12:08,240
There... There are no lotuses around here.

336
00:12:11,410 --> 00:12:11,980
Nezha.

337
00:12:12,720 --> 00:12:13,740
Nezha? I'm Nezha?

338
00:12:15,620 --> 00:12:16,420
Are you tired?

339
00:12:17,100 --> 00:12:17,630
How about

340
00:12:18,480 --> 00:12:19,880
we sit here and rest a bit?

341
00:12:21,030 --> 00:12:21,620
Sure.

342
00:12:28,030 --> 00:12:28,490
Ranran.

343
00:12:29,170 --> 00:12:30,710
Wait for me a second.

344
00:12:30,940 --> 00:12:31,960
W-Where are you going?

345
00:12:31,960 --> 00:12:32,790
Just wait a second.

346
00:12:32,790 --> 00:12:33,850
I'll be right back.

347
00:12:47,340 --> 00:12:47,800
Ranran.

348
00:12:48,730 --> 00:12:49,580
Didn't you say

349
00:12:49,580 --> 00:12:50,980
you wanted a soda?

350
00:12:51,670 --> 00:12:53,240
I found a grocery store over there.

351
00:12:53,240 --> 00:12:54,640
They happened to sell it.

352
00:12:54,670 --> 00:12:55,870
Let's drink and chat.

353
00:12:59,790 --> 00:13:00,870
Thank you.

354
00:13:05,750 --> 00:13:06,590
It's so sweet.

355
00:13:07,700 --> 00:13:10,030
Let's drink for a while before going back.

356
00:13:10,770 --> 00:13:11,600
Don't they say a chat

357
00:13:11,600 --> 00:13:13,730
lasts for the time of an incense stick?

358
00:13:13,890 --> 00:13:14,550
The two of us

359
00:13:16,070 --> 00:13:17,730
can chat for the time of a coil.

360
00:13:18,740 --> 00:13:20,740
Where did you get the mosquito coil?

361
00:13:21,240 --> 00:13:22,960
When I bought the soda,

362
00:13:23,000 --> 00:13:24,620
I thought there must be many

363
00:13:24,620 --> 00:13:25,950
mosquitoes by the lake.

364
00:13:26,150 --> 00:13:27,280
I figured

365
00:13:28,500 --> 00:13:30,260
I couldn't let you get bitten.

366
00:13:31,050 --> 00:13:32,890
Our chat shouldn't end with us

367
00:13:33,290 --> 00:13:35,220
covered in mosquito bites, right?

368
00:13:35,770 --> 00:13:37,170
This coil of incense will

369
00:13:37,770 --> 00:13:38,970
give us some time too.

370
00:13:44,620 --> 00:13:46,000
What do you think of me?

371
00:13:49,530 --> 00:13:50,460
You're alright.

372
00:13:54,480 --> 00:13:55,410
That's it?

373
00:13:56,320 --> 00:13:58,320
We have a whole coil's worth of time.

374
00:13:58,750 --> 00:13:59,950
Elaborate a bit more.

375
00:14:03,550 --> 00:14:06,010
At first, when we were at the small hostel,

376
00:14:06,010 --> 00:14:07,410
I thought you were just

377
00:14:07,820 --> 00:14:08,910
a smooth talker

378
00:14:08,910 --> 00:14:10,240
and didn't seem decent.

379
00:14:12,410 --> 00:14:13,740
But I felt that you were definitely

380
00:14:13,740 --> 00:14:14,840
not a bad person.

381
00:14:16,120 --> 00:14:18,240
What surprised me most was that

382
00:14:18,910 --> 00:14:19,890
you, a Beijing local,

383
00:14:19,890 --> 00:14:21,550
actually lived in a basement.

384
00:14:23,600 --> 00:14:25,670
It's a long story.

385
00:14:26,650 --> 00:14:27,580
Tell me about it.

386
00:14:30,360 --> 00:14:32,670
I'll keep it short.

387
00:14:33,790 --> 00:14:35,460
Well, my dad and I

388
00:14:36,630 --> 00:14:37,890
had a little conflict.

389
00:14:38,170 --> 00:14:38,720
Basically,

390
00:14:38,720 --> 00:14:39,770
what he wants me to do

391
00:14:39,770 --> 00:14:40,830
and what I want to do

392
00:14:40,980 --> 00:14:42,590
are never on the same page.

393
00:14:43,100 --> 00:14:43,720
And then,

394
00:14:43,720 --> 00:14:45,700
he kept finding ways to lecture me.

395
00:14:45,720 --> 00:14:46,890
I got annoyed by all the talk.

396
00:14:46,890 --> 00:14:48,450
But I know him.

397
00:14:49,030 --> 00:14:49,360
He

398
00:14:50,240 --> 00:14:51,840
certainly wouldn't harm me.

399
00:14:52,320 --> 00:14:53,150
One thing led to another,

400
00:14:53,150 --> 00:14:54,750
and I didn't want to live at home anymore.

401
00:14:54,750 --> 00:14:55,940
So I moved out.

402
00:14:56,650 --> 00:14:58,270
That's about it.

403
00:15:00,550 --> 00:15:01,130
I see.

404
00:15:02,890 --> 00:15:04,290
That's not complicated.

405
00:15:05,290 --> 00:15:06,530
Don't you want to persuade me?

406
00:15:06,530 --> 00:15:07,990
Why should I persuade you?

407
00:15:08,150 --> 00:15:09,080
You're well aware

408
00:15:09,080 --> 00:15:10,210
that they mean well.

409
00:15:10,720 --> 00:15:12,490
Besides, the world is so big.

410
00:15:12,630 --> 00:15:13,770
Not everyone's opinions

411
00:15:13,770 --> 00:15:15,030
can be on the same page.

412
00:15:15,910 --> 00:15:16,930
And

413
00:15:17,530 --> 00:15:18,990
as long as no one gets hurt,

414
00:15:19,340 --> 00:15:21,600
understanding is the highest standard.

415
00:15:25,480 --> 00:15:26,910
Out of everyone I've ever met,

416
00:15:26,910 --> 00:15:28,110
not including my mom,

417
00:15:29,080 --> 00:15:32,530
you're the woman of the highest standard.

418
00:15:34,620 --> 00:15:36,310
What are you talking about?

419
00:15:37,460 --> 00:15:38,460
When I first

420
00:15:38,460 --> 00:15:39,320
met you,

421
00:15:39,360 --> 00:15:41,220
I thought you were really pretty.

422
00:15:41,270 --> 00:15:41,830
Later,

423
00:15:42,240 --> 00:15:42,820
as I

424
00:15:42,820 --> 00:15:44,310
slowly got to know you,

425
00:15:44,750 --> 00:15:46,010
I realized you're even more

426
00:15:46,010 --> 00:15:47,410
beautiful on the inside.

427
00:15:48,170 --> 00:15:49,400
I know I'm not

428
00:15:49,480 --> 00:15:50,360
that outstanding.

429
00:15:50,360 --> 00:15:52,010
But I really hope that

430
00:15:52,750 --> 00:15:54,240
if you have anything to say,

431
00:15:54,240 --> 00:15:55,120
or when you're upset,

432
00:15:55,120 --> 00:15:56,410
you can talk to me.

433
00:15:56,500 --> 00:15:58,430
And if you run into any trouble,

434
00:15:58,820 --> 00:15:59,670
I can help you.

435
00:16:00,130 --> 00:16:00,510
What I'm

436
00:16:00,510 --> 00:16:01,460
trying to say is

437
00:16:02,170 --> 00:16:03,970
I like you.
[T/N: muffled voice]

438
00:16:05,770 --> 00:16:07,050
I like you.
[T/N: muffled voice]

439
00:16:07,050 --> 00:16:07,480
Um...

440
00:16:07,500 --> 00:16:07,840
I...

441
00:16:08,110 --> 00:16:09,340
I have things to do tomorrow.

442
00:16:09,340 --> 00:16:10,140
I've got to go.

443
00:16:10,370 --> 00:16:10,840
Ranran.

444
00:16:11,770 --> 00:16:14,170
T-This coil of incense isn't finished yet.

445
00:16:15,440 --> 00:16:17,770
Put it out.
We can light it again next time.

446
00:16:18,240 --> 00:16:18,860
Wait.

447
00:16:19,440 --> 00:16:21,400
Let's walk and talk.

448
00:16:23,620 --> 00:16:27,750
[Seasons Change Hostel]

449
00:16:25,410 --> 00:16:26,270
Feuds can

450
00:16:27,100 --> 00:16:27,960
cause de...

451
00:16:28,580 --> 00:16:31,450
Cause the living to die,

452
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:34,070
and the dead to live.

453
00:16:35,370 --> 00:16:36,860
When I no longer obz...

454
00:16:37,840 --> 00:16:38,900
When I no longer...

455
00:16:40,410 --> 00:16:41,090
Gosh.

456
00:16:41,340 --> 00:16:41,960
Whenever I recite lines,

457
00:16:41,960 --> 00:16:43,910
I mix up my nasal sounds.

458
00:16:44,510 --> 00:16:45,580
It's so annoying.

459
00:16:45,670 --> 00:16:46,530
Practice more.

460
00:16:50,790 --> 00:16:53,010
When I no longer obsess over love...

461
00:17:02,440 --> 00:17:04,680
Didn't you go to the film set?

462
00:17:04,960 --> 00:17:05,890
Why are you back?

463
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:09,250
I'm just a nobody.

464
00:17:09,310 --> 00:17:10,910
The crew didn't give me a bed.

465
00:17:11,010 --> 00:17:13,020
The assistant director
told me to find some scenes

466
00:17:13,020 --> 00:17:15,329
portraying a range of emotions
for auditions.

467
00:17:15,329 --> 00:17:17,440
I've read through the script
a million times,

468
00:17:17,440 --> 00:17:19,069
but it still feels like
something is missing.

469
00:17:19,069 --> 00:17:19,640
What?

470
00:17:20,089 --> 00:17:21,640
You're nitpicking their script now?

471
00:17:21,640 --> 00:17:23,099
No, that's not what I mean.

472
00:17:23,200 --> 00:17:24,569
The... The entire script

473
00:17:24,569 --> 00:17:26,349
is great when read as a whole.

474
00:17:26,770 --> 00:17:27,920
But if you pick out single scenes,

475
00:17:27,920 --> 00:17:30,250
it somewhat feels disjointed.

476
00:17:30,500 --> 00:17:32,360
I don't know which part to choose.

477
00:17:32,500 --> 00:17:33,660
Aid the emotions...

478
00:17:33,660 --> 00:17:35,090
Oh, I get it now.

479
00:17:40,440 --> 00:17:41,980
Human emotions...

480
00:17:44,880 --> 00:17:46,010
And uniqueness.

481
00:17:47,380 --> 00:17:48,040
Xu Shengli.

482
00:17:48,660 --> 00:17:50,320
Look at this painting of mine.

483
00:17:52,250 --> 00:17:55,230
Your painting is quite avant-garde.

484
00:17:55,980 --> 00:17:57,170
What are you doing?

485
00:17:58,090 --> 00:17:58,500
Look.

486
00:17:58,500 --> 00:18:00,070
If the two people in my painting

487
00:18:00,070 --> 00:18:01,290
were both grinning

488
00:18:01,290 --> 00:18:02,160
and laughing,

489
00:18:02,550 --> 00:18:04,180
they'd look like 2 nutjobs.

490
00:18:04,740 --> 00:18:05,680
But if between the two of them,

491
00:18:05,680 --> 00:18:06,570
one is crying

492
00:18:06,570 --> 00:18:07,700
and the other is laughing,

493
00:18:07,700 --> 00:18:08,480
then when you look at it,

494
00:18:08,480 --> 00:18:10,210
there's room for imagination.

495
00:18:10,570 --> 00:18:11,370
But...

496
00:18:11,470 --> 00:18:13,570
Wait, just... keep it simple.

497
00:18:15,940 --> 00:18:17,050
There was a great painter
in the late Ming Dynasty

498
00:18:17,050 --> 00:18:17,810
named Zhu Da.

499
00:18:18,290 --> 00:18:19,820
His alias was Bada Shanren.

500
00:18:19,960 --> 00:18:21,330
Take his signature, for example.

501
00:18:21,330 --> 00:18:22,480
The writing on top

502
00:18:22,610 --> 00:18:24,080
looks like "cry",

503
00:18:24,330 --> 00:18:25,330
and the writing on the bottom

504
00:18:25,330 --> 00:18:26,520
looks like "laugh".

505
00:18:26,720 --> 00:18:28,400
So there is laughter in tears,

506
00:18:28,400 --> 00:18:29,660
and tears in laughter.

507
00:18:29,740 --> 00:18:31,110
My inspiration for painting

508
00:18:31,110 --> 00:18:31,900
comes from there.

509
00:18:31,900 --> 00:18:32,420
I get it.

510
00:18:33,640 --> 00:18:34,920
You mean

511
00:18:34,920 --> 00:18:36,610
joy, anger, sorrow, and happiness

512
00:18:36,610 --> 00:18:38,010
shouldn't be separated?

513
00:18:38,220 --> 00:18:39,280
Joy within sorrow,

514
00:18:39,660 --> 00:18:40,930
and sorrow within joy.

515
00:18:41,810 --> 00:18:42,660
That way,

516
00:18:43,790 --> 00:18:44,790
it has more depth.

517
00:18:45,960 --> 00:18:47,280
You catch on quick.

518
00:18:47,770 --> 00:18:50,610
Not bad, Master Cao.

519
00:18:56,530 --> 00:18:57,420
How's it going?

520
00:19:03,390 --> 00:19:04,320
That won't do.

521
00:19:05,090 --> 00:19:06,090
Here, let me do it.

522
00:19:08,430 --> 00:19:10,360
There's ghosting.

523
00:19:11,330 --> 00:19:12,930
You pulled it back and forth?

524
00:19:14,590 --> 00:19:15,290
Watch me.

525
00:19:17,710 --> 00:19:18,290
Go.

526
00:19:21,390 --> 00:19:21,910
See?

527
00:19:22,660 --> 00:19:23,300
You try.

528
00:19:25,030 --> 00:19:26,770
Zongbao, how do you know everything?

529
00:19:26,770 --> 00:19:27,960
I'm an actor.

530
00:19:27,990 --> 00:19:29,400
I have to know a bit of everything.

531
00:19:29,400 --> 00:19:30,880
I need to learn from you then.

532
00:19:30,880 --> 00:19:33,340
Screenwriters need to know everything too.

533
00:19:34,760 --> 00:19:36,800
It's tough working in this crew.

534
00:19:37,050 --> 00:19:39,180
I'm new here. Still have a lot to learn.

535
00:19:42,940 --> 00:19:44,070
How's the director?

536
00:19:44,810 --> 00:19:46,670
Did he read your script?

537
00:19:49,270 --> 00:19:50,510
To be honest,

538
00:19:50,550 --> 00:19:52,210
I've been in the crew for days,

539
00:19:52,380 --> 00:19:53,380
but I haven't even seen

540
00:19:53,380 --> 00:19:54,510
the back of his head.

541
00:19:55,640 --> 00:19:56,460
Film crews...

542
00:19:57,510 --> 00:19:59,380
are too busy—there's too much going on.

543
00:19:59,380 --> 00:20:00,680
Every time I go,

544
00:20:01,110 --> 00:20:02,160
I see those people,

545
00:20:02,160 --> 00:20:03,530
and they all seem very busy.

546
00:20:03,530 --> 00:20:05,410
If you really want to stay,

547
00:20:05,550 --> 00:20:07,610
you have to make people remember you.

548
00:20:10,070 --> 00:20:10,530
Come on.

549
00:20:12,200 --> 00:20:13,800
Call me if you need anything.

550
00:20:26,570 --> 00:20:27,360
Hello.

551
00:20:27,420 --> 00:20:29,210
The PA in your crew,

552
00:20:29,250 --> 00:20:30,000
named Xu Shengli.

553
00:20:30,000 --> 00:20:30,980
Where is he?

554
00:20:32,310 --> 00:20:32,970
Over there.

555
00:20:33,220 --> 00:20:34,050
Okay, thanks.

556
00:20:34,510 --> 00:20:35,170
No problem.

557
00:20:40,070 --> 00:20:41,400
Great Screenwriter Xu.

558
00:20:43,110 --> 00:20:43,820
Ranran?

559
00:20:44,200 --> 00:20:45,170
Why are you here?

560
00:20:45,250 --> 00:20:47,050
I'm doing a makeup test
for Director Ma's crew.

561
00:20:47,050 --> 00:20:48,700
They said Director Weng's
team is next door.

562
00:20:48,700 --> 00:20:50,030
I guessed you'd be here.

563
00:20:52,900 --> 00:20:54,360
Is this all you're eating?

564
00:20:54,740 --> 00:20:55,460
Well, I...

565
00:20:55,830 --> 00:20:58,160
I'm rushing to write something. It's due.

566
00:20:59,090 --> 00:21:00,550
If Zhuang Zhuang knew about this,

567
00:21:00,550 --> 00:21:01,860
she'd be heartbroken.

568
00:21:02,810 --> 00:21:04,250
Have a seat.

569
00:21:13,530 --> 00:21:16,030
Something's been off
between you two lately.

570
00:21:16,030 --> 00:21:16,640
Tell me.

571
00:21:17,900 --> 00:21:19,100
How did you upset her?

572
00:21:19,700 --> 00:21:22,230
What could possibly be off
between me and her?

573
00:21:24,420 --> 00:21:26,000
What's wrong with Zhuang Zhuang?

574
00:21:26,000 --> 00:21:26,610
Is that guy from Wenzhou

575
00:21:26,610 --> 00:21:27,370
bullying her again?

576
00:21:27,370 --> 00:21:28,900
I knew you would

577
00:21:28,900 --> 00:21:29,590
bring that up.

578
00:21:29,590 --> 00:21:30,270
Let me tell you,

579
00:21:30,270 --> 00:21:32,250
there is nothing going on between them.

580
00:21:32,250 --> 00:21:33,940
She's sick of him.

581
00:21:47,590 --> 00:21:48,670
Listen.

582
00:21:48,830 --> 00:21:50,590
